8
00:01:02,720 --> 00:01:04,470
What's going on?

9
00:01:06,280 --> 00:01:08,300
Well, you see...

10
00:01:11,900 --> 00:01:14,100
It's as you see.

11
00:01:14,100 --> 00:01:15,850
We are dating.

12
00:01:17,560 --> 00:01:19,270
What?

13
00:01:19,270 --> 00:01:21,320
So...

14
00:01:21,320 --> 00:01:24,230
what happened was...

15
00:01:27,030 --> 00:01:30,310
Never! You're tricking me, right?

16
00:01:30,310 --> 00:01:32,960
Don't joke around like that.

17
00:01:36,770 --> 00:01:38,730
We aren't joking.

18
00:01:42,650 --> 00:01:45,360
Have you gone crazy? Get away from her!

19
00:01:46,600 --> 00:01:48,620
It's Yoon Joo Won.

20
00:01:48,620 --> 00:01:50,710
She's our sister.

21
00:01:50,710 --> 00:01:53,630
I said she's our sister!

22
00:02:12,970 --> 00:02:15,480
Kim San Ha lost his sanity for a moment.

23
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:17,510
He will be fine tomorrow morning.

24
00:02:17,510 --> 00:02:20,160
I'll scold him tomorrow, so just forget this whole thing.

25
00:02:21,950 --> 00:02:23,680
Sorry...

26
00:02:24,870 --> 00:02:27,430
for not telling you sooner.

27
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:30,890
We weren't trying to deceive you.

28
00:02:31,790 --> 00:02:34,920
Our dads don't know yet

29
00:02:36,950 --> 00:02:38,690
and...

30
00:02:40,860 --> 00:02:43,530
it hasn't been long since we started dating.

31
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:47,630
"We"?

32
00:02:49,030 --> 00:02:50,720
Kang Hae Joon.

33
00:02:52,420 --> 00:02:55,140
You said you and I couldn't.

34
00:02:55,140 --> 00:02:56,670
Because I'm your oppa.

35
00:02:56,670 --> 00:02:58,760
You are!

36
00:02:59,760 --> 00:03:02,450
Then Kim San Ha is your oppa, too.

37
00:03:02,450 --> 00:03:04,990
He's your oppa, just like I am.

38
00:03:04,990 --> 00:03:09,620
We have different surnames and are not blood-related, but we are still your brothers!

39
00:03:09,620 --> 00:03:15,220
Hae Joon, Joo Won and I really like each other.

40
00:03:15,220 --> 00:03:17,730
What about me?

41
00:03:22,790 --> 00:03:25,640
Why am I always getting abandoned?

42
00:03:31,220 --> 00:03:33,420
Who's abandoning–

43
00:03:39,100 --> 00:03:41,060
I'll go.

44
00:03:49,460 --> 00:03:52,600
- Nice catch. 
 - Yes.

45
00:03:54,350 --> 00:03:55,980
Where is Sunbae Hae Joon?

46
00:03:55,980 --> 00:03:58,100
He went to get beer from our house.

47
00:03:58,100 --> 00:04:01,270
Kim San Ha and Kang Hae Joon won't be coming any time soon.

48
00:04:01,270 --> 00:04:02,910
Why not?

49
00:04:02,910 --> 00:04:04,020
Later.

50
00:04:04,020 --> 00:04:06,420
We can't drink anymore anyway.

51
00:04:06,420 --> 00:04:07,920
Get up! Let's go home.

52
00:04:07,920 --> 00:04:11,140
Yes, let's go.

53
00:04:14,950 --> 00:04:17,730
Do you really like Hae Joon?

54
00:04:17,730 --> 00:04:19,510
- Pardon? 
 - Gosh.

55
00:04:19,510 --> 00:04:22,210
Hui Joo also still pines for Hae Joon.

56
00:04:22,210 --> 00:04:24,390
Why is everyone head over heels for Hae Joon?

57
00:04:24,390 --> 00:04:26,300
Sunbae is drunk.

58
00:04:26,300 --> 00:04:27,860
- Hurry and take him home. 
 - Yes.

59
00:04:27,860 --> 00:04:29,110
I'm not.

60
00:04:29,110 --> 00:04:31,220
I'm a hundred times more handsome.

61
00:04:31,220 --> 00:04:34,290
That's right. My baby is a thousand times more handsome.

62
00:04:34,290 --> 00:04:36,340
We are leaving.

63
00:04:36,340 --> 00:04:39,450
Okay, take care.

64
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:47,020
Why? What happened?

65
00:05:01,060 --> 00:05:02,730
Go away.

66
00:05:02,730 --> 00:05:04,730
I have nothing to say to you.

67
00:05:07,220 --> 00:05:10,110
You told me to open up just yesterday.

68
00:05:10,110 --> 00:05:14,450
Can't you think of how worried Joo Won will be if you leave like this?

69
00:05:17,540 --> 00:05:20,590
Did you follow me to ease your girlfriend's mind?

70
00:05:20,590 --> 00:05:22,250
Get lost.

71
00:05:22,250 --> 00:05:25,000
Joo Won and I said we were dating.

72
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:28,370
Why do you say you're being abandoned?

73
00:05:33,260 --> 00:05:36,600
You're Ahjusshi's son, and Joo Won is Dad's daughter.

74
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:39,580
If you two get married, you all become family.

75
00:05:39,580 --> 00:05:42,690
As the outsider, I'm nothing now.

76
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:45,700
How smart.

77
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:48,400
You thought that far in such a short time.

78
00:05:49,190 --> 00:05:50,890
Get lost.

79
00:05:50,890 --> 00:05:52,600
You annoy me.

80
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:56,150
So do you think we'd discard you, saying we no longer need you?

81
00:05:57,740 --> 00:06:00,670
Yes. That's right.

82
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:05,070
My dad abandoned me before I was even born.

83
00:06:05,070 --> 00:06:07,040
 My mom abandoned me. 

84
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:12,160
 My dad took me, then abandoned me again. 

85
00:06:16,080 --> 00:06:18,630
That's just how my life is, isn't it?

86
00:06:22,290 --> 00:06:24,120
Go, then.

87
00:06:25,820 --> 00:06:30,360
If you think that's the sort of people we are, then go.

88
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:34,950
I have no intention of begging you to trust us.

89
00:06:45,350 --> 00:06:46,480
   

90
00:06:46,480 --> 00:06:49,500
I can understand how Hae Joon feels.

91
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:55,020
I knew he was sad because of Ahjumma, but I didn't know it was this bad.

92
00:06:55,810 --> 00:06:59,090
That's because he didn't want you to know.

93
00:06:59,090 --> 00:07:00,980
What?

94
00:07:00,980 --> 00:07:02,590
It's nothing.

95
00:07:02,590 --> 00:07:05,860
San Ha will comfort him and bring him back, right?

96
00:07:14,030 --> 00:07:16,050
What happened? Where's Kang Hae Joon?

97
00:07:16,050 --> 00:07:17,420
Why are you alone?

98
00:07:17,420 --> 00:07:21,370
It's not like he's a teenager. He will return eventually.

99
00:07:24,750 --> 00:07:27,560
You should've consoled him and brought him back.

100
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:29,120
Where did he go?

101
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:31,150
There's nowhere to go alone at this hour.

102
00:07:31,150 --> 00:07:32,320
Did he go to Dad?

103
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:34,800
He wouldn't have, afraid he'd worry him.

104
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:36,810
Don't worry.

105
00:07:36,810 --> 00:07:39,470
He probably wants to be alone right now.

106
00:07:40,290 --> 00:07:42,670
He will be okay, right?

107
00:07:42,670 --> 00:07:44,060
Of course.

108
00:07:44,060 --> 00:07:46,520
I'll go.

109
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:53,970
By the way, since when did you find out we were dating?

110
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:58,800
There's probably nothing Dal doesn't know.

111
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:00,200
Bye.

112
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:34,160
♫  Even if you don't say where it hurts  ♫

113
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:37,400
♫  I know  ♫

114
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:43,160
♫  Like a wildflower growing on its own  ♫

115
00:08:43,160 --> 00:08:51,300
♫  The love I've kept hidden hurts  ♫

116
00:08:55,700 --> 00:09:02,410
♫  My wish, as it's smaller than my height  ♫

117
00:09:02,410 --> 00:09:09,350
♫  I can't be the tree that you can take shelter under  ♫

118
00:09:09,350 --> 00:09:12,800
♫  But like the warm sun  ♫

119
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:17,070
♫  Like the beautiful moon  ♫

120
00:09:17,070 --> 00:09:30,240
♫  I will always, as I have always done, be with you  ♫

